			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">SMN/BRD really wouldn't work.  First of all, summons don't do good damage at all until level 70.  So, that limits a SMN/BRD to just using Aerial Armor/Earthen Ward once a minute.  What would you do between blood pacts?  Have your avatar melee?  Your PT depends on SMN to be able to heal.  A PT needs a healer, and if a SMN isn't healing, they'll be better off getting a WHM to heal.  
<br />

<br />
Subbing BRD is a big no-no for exp PTs (except in one case).  First, you will be limited to only ONE bard song.  I know what you are thinking... you could ballad the mages and give attack or accuracy to the melee. Well, the ballad thing could work, but the strength of the attack+ or acc+ song will be weak, since you can ONLY sing and it will be capped at half your level.   RDM/BRD can work in certain PTs... you'll get 4mp/tick <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
It is somewhat unfortunately, but SMN are limited to subbing WHM or doomed to sit in Jeuno.  If you aren't SMN/WHM, a PT could find somethig better <img src="images/smiles/icon_sad.gif" alt="icon_sad.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
